Checchi Capital Advisers LLC Boosts Stake in Nike, Inc. (NKE)


					Posted by Charlotte Bryant on Jul 22nd, 2017 // No Comments




Checchi Capital Advisers LLC increased its position in  Nike, Inc. (NYSE:NKE) by 6.2% during the first quarter, according to its most recent Form 13F filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). The institutional investor  owned 14,652 shares of the footwear maker’s stock after buying an additional 856 shares during the period. Checchi Capital Advisers LLC’s holdings in Nike were worth $817,000 at the end of the most recent reporting period. 
Several other institutional investors also recently bought and sold shares of the company. Jennison Associates LLC increased its stake in shares of  Nike by 124.7% in the first quarter. Jennison Associates LLC now owns 25,143,559 shares of the footwear maker’s stock worth $1,401,251,000 after buying an additional 13,953,567 shares during the period.  Norges Bank acquired a new stake in shares of  Nike during the fourth quarter worth about $463,411,000.  DZ BANK AG Deutsche Zentral Genossenschafts Bank Frankfurt am Main acquired a new stake in shares of  Nike during the fourth quarter worth about $165,446,000.  State Street Corp increased its stake in shares of  Nike by 4.6% in the fourth quarter. State Street Corp now owns 58,719,250 shares of the footwear maker’s stock worth $2,984,719,000 after buying an additional 2,563,166 shares during the period.  Finally, Asset Management One Co. Ltd. increased its stake in shares of  Nike by 769.8% in the fourth quarter. Asset Management One Co. Ltd. now owns 2,306,093 shares of the footwear maker’s stock worth $117,260,000 after buying an additional 2,040,975 shares during the period. 63.98% of the stock is owned by hedge funds and other institutional investors. 


 Get Nike Inc. alerts:



Nike, Inc. (NKE) traded up 1.44% on Friday, hitting $59.95. 11,048,297 shares of the company’s stock traded hands. Nike, Inc. has a one year low of $49.01 and a one year high of $60.33. The stock has a 50-day moving average of $55.02 and a 200-day moving average of $54.92. The stock has a market cap of $98.73 billion, a PE ratio of 23.88 and a beta of 0.60. 





Nike (NYSE:NKE) last posted its earnings results on Thursday, June 29th. The footwear maker reported $0.60 earnings per share for the quarter, beating the consensus estimate of $0.50 by $0.10. The company had revenue of $8.68 billion for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $8.63 billion. Nike had a net margin of 12.34% and a return on equity of 34.18%. Nike’s revenue was up 5.3% on a year-over-year basis. During the same period in the previous year, the business posted $0.49 EPS.  On average, equities analysts forecast that  Nike, Inc. will post $2.43 earnings per share for the current fiscal year. 
The firm also recently announced a quarterly dividend, which was paid on Wednesday, July 5th. Investors of record on Monday, June 5th were paid a dividend of $0.18 per share. This represents a $0.72 annualized dividend and a yield of 1.20%. The ex-dividend date  was Thursday, June 1st. Nike’s payout ratio is currently 28.69%. 
